{"word":"ἀποκάμνω","slug":"ἀποκάμνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποκάμνω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to grow quite weary, fail</i> or <i>flag utterly</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <el>ἀπ. ζητῶν</el> <i>to be quite weary of</i> seeking, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to cease</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>ἀπ. πόνον</el> <i>to flinch from toil</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}